In [38]:
df = pd.read_csv('results_DQN_model_1.csv')


#Storing the different columns in variables
episodes = df['episode']
epsilon = df['epsilon']
score = df['score']
average_score=df['average_score']
total_reward=df['total_reward']
average_reward=df['average_reward']


plt.title("DQN : Scores (Training)",fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Episode",fontsize=13)
plt.ylabel("Score",fontsize=13)
plt.plot(episodes,score,'c-')

#PLotting min and max values
ymax=max(score)
ymin=min(score)

#xmin
xmin = df.loc[df['score']==ymin]

if xmin.shape[0]>1:
    xmin=(xmin.iloc[[0]]) 
              

xmin = min(xmin['episode'])


#xmax
xmax = df.loc[df['score']==ymax]

if xmax.shape[0]>1:
    xmax=(xmax.iloc[[0]]) 
              
xmax=max(xmax['episode'])

#plotting min coordinates
plt.plot(xmin,ymin,'r.')
plt.text(xmin + 2,ymin,'min('+str(xmin)+','+str(ymin)+')',fontsize=11)

#plotting max coordinates
plt.plot(xmax,ymax,'r.')
plt.text(xmax + 2,ymax,'max('+str(xmax)+','+str(ymax)+')',fontsize=11)

plt.savefig('outputs/dql_score.png')
plt.show()

In [42]:
df3 = pd.read_csv('results_Q_cartpole.csv')


#Storing the different columns in variables
episode3 = df3['episode']
epsilon3 = df3['epsilon']
score3 = df3['score']
average_score3=df3['average_score']
total_reward3=df3['total_reward']
average_reward3=df3['average_reward']
table_length = df3['Q_table_length']



#total Score
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,9))

ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((1,1),(0,0))

ax1.set_title("Q-Learning : Scores (Training)",fontsize=20)
ax1.set_xlabel("Episode",fontsize=18)
ax1.set_ylabel("Score",fontsize=18)
ax1.plot(episode3,score3,'c-',linewidth="0.5")


#PLotting min and max values
ymax=max(score3)
ymin=min(score3)

#xmin
xmin = df3.loc[df3['score']==ymin]

if xmin.shape[0]>1:
    xmin=(xmin.iloc[[0]]) 
              
xmin = min(xmin['episode'])


#xmax
xmax = df3.loc[df3['score']==ymax]

if xmax.shape[0]>1:
    xmax=(xmax.iloc[[0]]) 
              
xmax=max(xmax['episode'])

#plotting min coordinates
plt.plot(xmin,ymin,'r.')
plt.text(xmin + 2,ymin,'min('+str(xmin)+','+str(round(ymin,2))+')',fontsize=15)

#plotting max coordinates
plt.plot(xmax,ymax,'r.')
plt.text(xmax + 2,ymax,'max('+str(xmax)+','+str(round(ymax,2))+')',fontsize=15)


plt.savefig('outputs/QL_score.png')
plt.show()

#Average Scores
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,9))

ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((1,1),(0,0))

ax1.set_title("Q-Learning : Average Score(Training)",fontsize=20)
ax1.set_xlabel("Episode",fontsize=18)
ax1.set_ylabel("Average Score",fontsize=18)
ax1.plot(episode3,average_score3,'b-',linewidth="0.7")


#PLotting min and max values
ymax=max(average_score3)
ymin=min(average_score3)

#xmin
xmin = df3.loc[df3['average_score']==ymin]

if xmin.shape[0]>1:
    xmin=(xmin.iloc[[0]]) 
              
xmin = min(xmin['episode'])


#xmax
xmax = df3.loc[df3['average_score']==ymax]

if xmax.shape[0]>1:
    xmax=(xmax.iloc[[0]]) 
              
xmax=max(xmax['episode'])

#plotting min coordinates
plt.plot(xmin,ymin,'r.')
plt.text(xmin + 2,ymin,'min('+str(xmin)+','+str(round(ymin,2))+')',fontsize=15)

#plotting max coordinates
plt.plot(xmax,ymax,'r.')
plt.text(xmax + 2,ymax,'max('+str(xmax)+','+str(round(ymax,2))+')',fontsize=15)

#plotting the final co-ordinates

y_final = df3['average_score'][x_final]
plt.plot(x_final,y_final,'r.')
plt.text(x_final + 2,y_final,'final('+str(x_final)+','+str(round(y_final,2))+')',fontsize=15)

plt.show()
